{
  "texts": [
    "• Chen & Lee (2024).",
    "Following the standard efficient parameter configuration, we integrate it into TRADES with m = 1-8 and k = 10 (10-step attack).",
    "All models are evaluated using three categories of metrics: PR, AR evaluation, and GE.",
    "• PR Evaluation: We evaluate PR using two metrics: PR D (γ), computed at four radii (8/255, 0.08, 0.1, and 0.12) to assess robustness under increasing perturbation levels (for MNIST, the radii are: 0.3, 0.35, 0.4, 0.45), and ProbAcc(ρ), with three tolerance levels ρ (0.01, 0.05, 0.1).",
    "PR evaluations are performed by sampling 100 points from the perturbation region for each test example."
  ]
}